TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Multiplicity of Institutional Logics and the Heterogeneity of Organizational Responses
AU  - Greenwood, Royston
AU  - Díaz, Amalia Magán
AU  - Li, Stan Xiao
AU  - Lorente, José Céspedes
Y1  - 2009/08/31
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2010/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/orsc.1090.0453
DO  - 10.1287/orsc.1090.0453
T2  - Organization Science
JF  - Organization Science
JO  - Organization Science
SP  - 521
EP  - 539
VL  - 21
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper shows that organizations in market settings face complex institutional contexts to which they respond in different though patterned ways. We show how both regional state logics and family logics impact on organizational responses to an overarching market logic. Regional logics are particularly potent when the activities of firms, especially of large firms, are concentrated in regions whose governments champion regional distinctiveness and where the regional activities of the firm are significant. Family logics affect the decision to downsize, especially in smaller firms. This paper advances institutional theory by showing the influences of nonmarket institutions on market behavior, contributes to the growing recognition of community influences, and highlights the importance of historical context.
AB  - This paper shows that organizations in market settings face complex institutional contexts to which they respond in different though patterned ways. We show how both regional state logics and family logics impact on organizational responses to an overarching market logic. Regional logics are particularly potent when the activities of firms, especially of large firms, are concentrated in regions whose governments champion regional distinctiveness and where the regional activities of the firm are significant. Family logics affect the decision to downsize, especially in smaller firms. This paper advances institutional theory by showing the influences of nonmarket institutions on market behavior, contributes to the growing recognition of community influences, and highlights the importance of historical context.
